caller_intent: Greg Bailey is reporting water damage at a rental property (1706 Grant Avenue) and wants to understand the deductible for the policy under Esther May Myers' heirs to determine if filing a claim is worthwhile.
resolution_steps: Agent Jamie confirms the policy exists for Esther May Myers' heirs and notes a $1,000 deductible based on system data (though unable to verify directly due to technical issues).
Jamie advises Greg to assess the damage cost: if over $1,000, proceed with a claim; if under, avoid filing.
Explains the claims process: carrier will assign an adjuster to evaluate coverage and determine next steps.
knowledge_required: Understanding of insurance deductibles and claims processes
Ability to navigate internal policy management systems
Judgment on when to recommend filing a claim based on damage estimates
systems_referenced: Internal policy management software (with technical issues)
summary: Greg Bailey reported water damage at a rental property and sought clarity on the deductible for the policy. Agent Jamie, despite system issues, estimated a $1,000 deductible and advised filing a claim if repairs exceed that amount. The call highlighted technical challenges with the policy management system and the need for carrier verification.
